detail.requirements:
• 3년 이상의 데이터 분석 관련 학력 또는 업무 경력이 있는 분; advanced data analytics를 배우고 real-world data에 apply하시고 싶은 분;
• MySQL, PostgreSQL query를 통해 big data 추출; 
• Google Analytics 4;
• Data import, manipulation, EDA, Regression Analysis, Machine Learning via R or Python;
• Neural Network, LLM training data preprocessing 및 hyperparameter tuning;
• ChatGPT, Claude Sonnet, Perplexity, 캐릭터 챗봇, Stable Diffusion, 등 다양한 AI 서비스 사용 경험이 많은 분;
• 면접 때 SQL 및 data analytics 과제 통과 하신 분;
•  영어 및 제2외국어 능통자 우대

• Three-plus years of data analytics related education or work experience; eager to learn advanced data analytics and apply it to real-world data; aptitude for quantitative reasoning and analysis;
• MySQL, PostgreSQL query to extract big data (BubbleTap, Inc.'s database tables contain, on average, millions of samples and hundreds of features); 
• Google Analytics 4;
• Data import, manipulation, EDA, Statistical Analysis, Machine Learning via R or Python;
• Neural Network, LLM training data preprocessing and hyperparameter tuning;
• Broad experience using various AI services such as ChatGPT, Claude Sonnet, Perplexity, Character Chatbot, Stable Diffusion, etc;
• Is eager to learn and apply the newest concepts in Machine Learning, Neural Networks, and data analysis;
• Satisfactory completion of SQL and data analytics tasks during the interview;
• Fluency in English is a must and fluency in a second foreign language is preferred.

detail.preferred_points:
• 주도적으로 업무를 수행할 수 있는 분
• 데이터 기반으로 조직을 설득하여 서비스를 개선한 경험이 있는 분
• 데이터 분석 관련학과(통계학, 수학, 산업공학 등)를 전공하신 분

We are looking for an individual who:
• can actively take the initiative as opposed to passively receiving tasks;
• can clearly and succinctly communicate data concepts to non-technical stakeholders;
• enjoys using a broad range of AI services for purposes of professional improvement, productivity increase, and personal enjoyment;
• has ties internationally for purposes of expanding BubbeTap Inc.'s services;
• if applicable, has Korean fluency equivalent to TOPIK 3 and above.
